        subheading:"Fans Laud Nandita Das' Zwigato Trailer, Call It Emotional & Realistic",
        description:"Kapil Sharma, a household name, might have hit the bull's eye with comedy, but did you know his first passion was singing. Often seen singing on his comedy show, Kapil was rejected from Indian Idol.  He is now accomplishing his other dream of becoming an actor. The man who made his acting debut with Abbas Mustan's romantic comedy Kis Kisko Pyaar Karoon will next be seen in Zwigato, which is about an ex-floor manager who loses his job during the pandemic and starts to work as a food delivery rider. The film showcases what struggles and troubles a delivery boy was to go through - a job that perhaps doesn't get as much empathy as it should. Some others even appreciated the dialogue. 'The quote, 'He a labourer, that's why he's helpless or maybe he's helpless, that's why he's a labourer.' This sounds so good. What a great writing this movie got.' A fan called him versatile. 'We should apreciate him for doing out of the box role being awesome in comedy also the character of his wife looks equally talented.Lots of love Kapil Bhai!' Some others praised Nandita Das as well. 'Hats off to Nandita Das for her wonderful direction .This type of film provides a great opportunity to showcase acting skills, and Kapil Pajji has nailed it. I loved it!'",
